      "site.fcffdf646b49cd9b55": "Diagnose and repair misconceptions.",
      "site.c02d9cb3085f209c10": "Diagnose, suggest revisions, invite learner choice, and iterate.",
      "site.176a42e182a0259915": "diagram labeling",
      "site.b512fdda71c74298d9": "Diagram Labeling Practice",
      "site.6142886e5753e67b6e": "Did the AI check your reasoning instead of simply replacing it?",
      "site.8bbc7accade6d600ca": "Did you answer at least one question before reading the correction?",
      "site.597bfef7720861d525": "Different jobs need different modes: Socratic questions, homework hints, flashcards, debate, history roleplay, writing critique, and more.",
      "site.210a67f212873c98b8": "Different learning jobs need different flows. Use a homework coach for hints, a math step coach for problem solving, a Socratic tutor for deep understanding, flashcards for recall, and quizzes for pressure-tested practice.",
      "site.54cbf7c267f2bc4b14": "Different learning jobs need different interaction shapes, so inspir uses active, mode-specific teaching. A homework hint, Socratic question, historical simulation, flashcard review, and writing critique should not behave like the same generic chat.",
      "site.87f1c595d44b5c8609": "Different learning jobs need different shapes: Socratic questions, homework hints, flashcards, debate, history roleplay, writing critique, and study planning.",
      "site.4446ba74c2780d08c6": "Different people need different AI learning routes.",
      "site.c118be4848fe4bc138": "Disallowed",
      "site.d05e90ca0e6c3ef173": "Disclaimer Of Warranty",
      "site.cb5d79e34e93ab171e": "Disclosure of Data",
      "site.0c6b43086d51acbcff": "Discover paths that fit you",
      "site.29c91e33ae3f9f5a5a": "Discover paths that fit you.",
      "site.950c582c14e6769170": "Dismiss language options",
      "site.1e18fb9a483e9c86aa": "Distribution that started offline",
      "site.b2940b1d694b32ae73": "Diverge, cluster, choose, refine, and make the idea actionable.",
      "site.a97e22fb658440c625": "DMCA Notice and Procedure for Copyright Infringement Claims",
      "site.85fd09bca3b8cf3b04": "Do I know what to practice next?",
      "site.23434ad4b2352cd83d": "Do not accept a revised paragraph until you can explain why the revision is better.",
      "site.124b5f6fab5e22f16c": "Do not act like a passive Q&A tutor or bury work in chat. Do not overpraise weak output. Keep the user as decision owner, preserve their voice in writing tasks, and end sessions with a concrete artifact or next action.",
      "site.1cff5085b8f8fd2b23": "Do not advance just because the learner clicked next. Require evidence, name misconceptions specifically, and repair weak links before moving on.",
      "site.d36ff525e788525eb8": "Do not amplify hateful or dangerous arguments. Reframe sensitive topics around evidence, ethics, and learning.",
      "site.761df0c823f13a98b5": "Do not ask for a complete summary before you know the prerequisite ideas.",
      "site.69575a35ac9be4e4c2": "Do not ask learners to run unsafe code. Explain security-sensitive code at a high level when needed.",
      "site.e5d9412dc19e3b731b": "Do not ask which product wins. Ask which learning behavior fits.",
      "site.6a58ac68ad823b0c4c": "Do not claim live verification without tools. Recommend checking primary sources for current facts.",
      "site.9fffdf38d1ff642493": "Do not complete graded work for the learner. Make them own the final response.",
      "site.0b64b0646ae04485d5": "Do not confuse a fast answer with mastery.",
      "site.c4559ce2b10f6ead02": "Do not debate only the side you already agree with.",
      "site.00aa0ce5925c3a4939": "Do not ignore hesitation; uncertainty is a useful signal for review.",
      "site.1cfe26fd6091601540": "Do not invent bibliographic details. Mark unknown fields clearly.",
      "site.76201fbb49370cf133": "Do not invent citations. Clearly mark when source verification is needed.",
      "site.21eada545bb8171328": "Do not lecture by default, ask multiple questions, hide progress, or dump the answer too soon. Use hint ladders before explanations. If the learner asks for direct explanation, give it concisely and then require a final synthesis in their own words. For medical, legal, financial, or sensitive decisions, include appropriate caution and avoid pushing a hidden conclusion.",
      "site.f5de131f08eb4bd5fa": "Do not let roleplay replace dates, context, documents, or evidence labels.",
      "site.a5242f3ba86cd9c0f0": "Do not make a plan that assumes every topic needs equal time.",
      "site.7d575017a3f23cd39a": "Do not make flashcards from sentences you still cannot explain in your own words.",
      "site.93a88b5002dec789a8": "Do not paste an assignment and ask for the finished response.",
      "site.7a4fd3d4db10921f4a": "Do not provide long copyrighted text. Work from user-provided excerpts or brief summaries.",
      "site.da4b7b46a4c5ec68f8": "Do not provide therapy or crisis counseling. Encourage trusted human support for serious distress.",
      "site.cf195d700b38555696": "Do not reproduce long copyrighted passages. Summarize user-provided text.",
      "site.3e1a706bca15d6e1cc": "Do not reread notes before testing what you can already recall.",
      "site.ca4405979b3215e903": "Do not review everything equally",
      "site.2b0be54e04c20db9c4": "Do not shame mistakes. For graded work, coach understanding rather than producing a submission.",
      "site.db0a85d5315d363264": "Do not skip showing what you already tried; the useful help depends on that context.",
      "site.1b7692a5742065c8fd": "Do not stop after the first explanation; make yourself answer questions about it.",
      "site.a2ad47724e94b66423": "Do not treat generated dialogue as a real quote or primary source.",
      "site.f328079c2a15303520": "Do something with it",
