      "site.b510debc2ba94dfda6": "Turn notes or topics into focused flashcards with hints, answers, examples, and common traps.",
      "site.477b50d4abd0da659b": "Turn the corrected mistake into a flashcard or short checklist for later.",
      "site.48a08f580119dbfd04": "Turn the explanation into active recall cards with one conceptual card, one example card, and one misconception card.",
      "site.ff1a7c17f19c22b5eb": "Turn the hardest missed question into a flashcard and review it later.",
      "site.148eb6fc9a6b1b8134": "Turn these missed questions into flashcards grouped by concept, formula, definition, and example.",
      "site.3e23220342351e6253": "Turn your syllabus, exam date, time, and weak areas into a practical study plan.",
      "site.3a056d0d453e66afed": "Understand a hard topic",
      "site.7142cc64953587182b": "Understand a historical context, question a perspective, compare claims, and separate simulation from documented fact.",
      "site.43417b2770a6aa9b4b": "Understand code, debug errors, learn programming concepts, and build small projects step by step.",
      "site.555550019c0610a389": "Unmute film",
      "site.5837baa2f3fd477b73": "Use AI as a coach for understanding, practice, and feedback instead of a shortcut that quietly removes the learning.",
      "site.e6ef6fb29b1c837901": "Use AI homework coaching for hints, step checks, math reasoning, and writing feedback while keeping the final work yours.",
      "site.9a8c3a87f33267391f": "Use AI time travel, historical conversations, and debate practice to explore context, evidence, arguments, and perspectives.",
      "site.ca2809d878b3d8d4bf": "use client",
      "site.1ae09bc3eef4a70662": "Use debate to compare the strongest claim and strongest counterclaim.",
      "site.981c30512d55fc31b6": "Use hints, step checks, and writing feedback without turning the learning into answer copying.",
      "site.7365f708ac121cec86": "Use inspir for essay feedback, reading support, speaking practice, source critique, and revision loops that improve structure without replacing the learner's voice.",
      "site.6aada9efddc2925e91": "Use inspir for homework hints, math step checks, writing feedback, source critique, Socratic questions, and flashcards without exposing private chats.",
      "site.5419b0585afa54c629": "Use inspir for step-by-step math help, homework hints, Socratic reasoning, quizzes, flashcards, and exam prep without answer-copying.",
      "site.0af3b33b94561f1ce4": "Use public guest modes for free, then explore the open-source work and school deployment paths.",
      "site.4cfe6ba8b15db0b7c1": "Use Socratic questions",
      "site.9963920c7bdac40912": "Use the exam date, syllabus, available time, and weak areas to create a plan that can survive real life.",
      "site.5917147366ea1099e5": "Use the linked guide, prompt, subject hub, or learning path to review the weak spot later.",
      "site.cedb4e92bf7b0e0fcc": "Use writing feedback for structure, clarity, and evidence while keeping the final draft recognizably yours.",
      "site.22ae52c971e1606ead": "Useful from the first click",
      "site.83d51c9d18fe71ac90": "Video controls",
