      "site.9884d6321db182435a": "Why a Socratic AI tutor can make ideas stick",
      "site.26e66d2c403929d540": "Why combine history with debate?",
      "site.cb3f19f849d9a614f6": "Why use Socratic questions after an explanation?",
      "site.b8a5730cebdd9b8c2d": "Work through algebra, calculus, word problems, and math concepts one step at a time with an AI coach.",
      "site.4e2149136bd53c413f": "Work through math steps",
      "site.3437548ca48afa1053": "Write a three-sentence explanation without looking, then ask the Socratic mode to find the weak link.",
      "site.2b690267ad064f9d94": "Write exactly where you got stuck before asking for help.",
      "site.2dabb8334b6cbbc196": "Writing",
      "site.031857a0f03861e726": "Writing Coach",
      "site.572dd800fbaae05945": "Yes, when it gives hints, checks reasoning, explains mistakes, and asks you to produce the final answer instead of writing it for you.",
      "site.4eb7825da66025f6ae": "Yes. Public topic chats such as Learn Anything, Socratic Instruction, Homework Coach, quizzes, and flashcards open directly in guest mode.",
      "site.8a7aa2b153eb463026": "Yes. Schools can use the public product first, then discuss custom AI learning spaces with school-specific workflows, confidentiality, and funded access options.",
      "site.7e0d4a8f0b3a3c531c": "Yes. The public guest learning modes are designed for free access, so learners can start without needing a school deployment or paid account.",
      "site.6ca3eede4c1406628d": "You can try public learning modes freely. Saved chats, accounts, admin tools, and user data stay private."
