      "site.4e594b58dd36d39315": "The best learning sessions are adjustable. This mode is tuned for vocabulary builder with its own prompts, examples, and learning flow.",
      "site.8d2a6330ca29a54056": "The best outcome is not a perfect answer. It is the moment a learner says, \"I think I get it now. Let me try.\"",
      "site.5b31482ac17c2a64c4": "The blog is organized around study methods, prompt loops, and the public AI learning modes people can use immediately.",
      "site.fe0adb314af0ba3715": "The blog should not be a dead end. Every cluster is designed to move a learner from advice into a mode, prompt loop, quiz, flashcard set, or revision habit.",
      "site.a0adf96de1375d5d48": "The coach gives targeted revision priorities and before-after examples without replacing your voice.",
      "site.cc04d54305bbe12e97": "The coach pushes one strong counterargument at a time and tracks the claims that matter.",
      "site.332d2bf8600d9fb327": "The coach supports your thinking without taking over the assignment, so the final work stays yours.",
      "site.091a1a8b1148439190": "The common idea is simple: keep the learner active. AI should make thinking easier to start, not unnecessary to do.",
      "site.f4a459004391d62ea6": "The copy trap is subtle. It does not always feel like cheating. Sometimes it feels like being efficient. The AI explains something beautifully, you nod along, and then you move on. Ten minutes later you cannot reproduce the idea without the answer in front of you.",
      "site.3e5edc20387b59f6c5": "The debate uses public style and worldview without pretending to know private beliefs.",
      "site.3b584307e059abea92": "The difference is how you use it.",
      "site.612f806fd20c077cb2": "The easiest version of an AI tutor is a box that gives polished answers. That is useful sometimes, but it is not enough. A learner who only receives answers can leave with the page finished and the skill unchanged.",
