      "site.fcff144343c86582f5": "self-taught learner",
      "site.200445f78f9de23900": "Self-taught learners need momentum and structure. inspir helps turn curiosity into a path: explain, build, test, review, and keep going.",
      "site.ab12d4c2183313c114": "Start a topic from first principles",
      "site.02d279ce2f7b58c890": "Start learning",
      "site.584903a264f3830b30": "Start with a simple explanation, then ask Socratic questions until you can explain it back.",
      "site.4d27a4365d4632bb55": "Start with Learn Anything for a simple explanation, Homework Coach for a stuck assignment, or Flashcard Builder when the goal is review.",
      "site.43a1c6e0d64cef2586": "Start with public guidance, then open the right mode.",
      "site.cc8d906e2386ecdc7f": "Start with the mode that matches the moment.",
      "site.bc3d4521c41cfb94c8": "Start with the public modes, then use the schools page to review deployment steps, use cases, and trust boundaries.",
      "site.cc90dc177fb091bed4": "Student homework, parent support, teacher evaluation, and self-study all need different framing.",
      "site.a90f77b9d0d006ce59": "Students need fast help, but the help still has to leave the thinking in their hands. inspir routes common study moments into focused public modes instead of one generic answer box.",
      "site.e20ba03a49837a67e2": "Students, parents, teachers, and independent learners need different kinds of support. These paths make the first step clearer.",
      "site.3f7326f7bef1a51c76": "Students, parents, teachers, and self-taught learners search for different things. These pages route each audience to the right public mode, guide, and study workflow.",
      "site.b8771030157c8d42e0": "Support writing while preserving voice",
      "site.bda68a0e93312745da": "Teachers need more than a generic chatbot. They need predictable learning behaviors: ask questions, check reasoning, generate practice, preserve student voice, and make misconceptions visible.",
      "site.1d737bc462fed10acb": "The audience pages make the expected learning behavior explicit so the first session starts with better judgment.",
      "site.92fcbd5b9f2add9f90": "The learning situations this hub helps with.",
      "site.a764f5185c460529c3": "The pages do not expose private conversations. They organize public modes, prompts, guides, workflows, and safety boundaries so a learner can start in the right place.",
      "site.697c3cdd7ed1c962a2": "The questions this page is designed to answer.",
      "site.a52b11b8c16d29c1d4": "The same AI tutor can be a homework hint, a parent-supervised explain-back loop, a teacher evaluation surface, or a self-study coach. The page should make that clear.",
      "site.be264fde5aa5eeda56": "The self-study challenge is not just finding information. It is choosing the next right action and knowing whether the idea actually stuck.",
      "site.4407fe7c1d3979a8c3": "The strongest student workflow is not answer-copying. It is a loop: explain the stuck point, ask one better question, get a hint, try again, then review the miss.",
      "site.fb9322818a19db40a9": "These are common ways people describe the same learning need.",
      "site.56c102082f5fde34c2": "These live guest modes are open to try. Private user conversations stay private.",
      "site.22b57b9f79b632bc89": "Turn confusion into a quiz or flashcard before moving on.",
      "site.90683218b2683484b4": "Turn mistakes into review",
      "site.cd9e3fb3c1c5e2b918": "Turn the first click into a complete learning loop.",
