      "site.798889c0e1a0e77074": "White-labelled AI tutoring for schools, with guest learning modes, custom workflows, confidentiality planning, NCERT-aligned options, and CSR sponsorship paths.",
      "site.0bab43340487200390": "White-labelled AI tutoring for schools, with guest learning modes, custom workflows, confidentiality planning, NCERT-aligned options, and funded access paths.",
      "site.ce76ad61efdaa2b7a3": "Who can use the media page?",
      "site.f4ff361d2bbe9cfce0": "Who it helps",
      "site.501e16edc5f5d250e7": "Why are public learning pages easy to share?",
      "site.cb75e42f757e62e655": "Why does inspir support school and partner deployments?",
      "site.1ecd92426534a2d5f6": "Why is inspir built around modes instead of one chat box?",
      "site.9b13983e2e1a6d9c81": "Yes. A school can begin by testing public modes, then move toward a pilot or tailored deployment when the use case, content needs, and funding path are clear.",
      "site.a4d26ae1b3500af2f6": "Yes. Public guest modes such as Learn Anything, Socratic Instruction, Homework Coach, quizzes, and flashcards open directly from simple /chat/{topicSlug} links.",
      "site.59a454af1a1e158bb2": "Yes. Public topic entrypoints such as /chat/learn-anything and /chat/socratic-instruction are open learning pages that anyone can try.",
