      "site.472db54c5bf1afe70c": "XP & Leveling",
      "site.039c20d60b55351619": "Yes, but the recommended workflow is hint-first. Use it to understand the method, check your work, and review errors instead of copying a final answer.",
      "site.737b9a139c968691f8": "Yes. Code Tutor can explain concepts, walk through examples, ask you to predict behavior, and help you practice without turning learning into copy-paste.",
      "site.56035a314152165c65": "Yes. Exam Prep Planner can turn your topics, date, and available time into a practical revision sequence with practice and review.",
      "site.99f395fa005717000f": "Yes. Quiz, Flashcard Builder, and Spaced Review are public modes designed for active recall and mistake repair.",
      "site.16a47c23ca93ec95ab": "Yes. Reading Companion can simplify passages, ask questions, explain vocabulary, and help you identify the main claim and supporting evidence.",
      "site.6dc1da75c795daff11": "Yes. Subject hubs are public pages built for learners. They expose only public learning guidance and public guest-mode links, not private saved chats.",
      "site.da400d3b29e0ba369d": "Yes. The historical person mode is a learning simulation for perspective and questioning. It should not be cited as an authenticated quotation.",
      "site.620eba277318f87eee": "Yes. The public Homework Coach is available at /chat/homework-coach, and this subject hub links to the supporting modes and guides.",
      "site.66115753297dc12bf0": "Yes. The recommended use is hints, explanations, step checks, feedback, and review prompts rather than final answers you cannot explain.",
      "site.00409f6901c6ae8ecc": "Yes. Use Time Travel for context, History Cause and Effect for argument structure, Debate for counterarguments, and Source Critic for evidence boundaries."
