      "site.3cb0dc27d87c29c430": "Debate with a personality prompts and study loop",
      "site.c7ade179f07b420526": "End with a recap you write yourself.",
      "site.6061c4a8bf7a6cbc31": "For Debate with a personality, a useful practice loop is:",
      "site.f75f75b80404676d62": "For this mode, the job is simple: Practice argument by debating a public or fictional personality on a topic you choose.",
      "site.c077bcb35f8f76b879": "Good prompts usually include three things: the subject, your current level, and the kind of help you want. You do not need perfect wording. You only need enough context for the session to begin.",
      "site.3cb8399fd818707e38": "If the response feels too broad, narrow it. Ask for one example, one misconception, one check question, or one next step. If it feels too easy, ask for a challenge. If it feels too hard, ask for a bridge from what you already know.",
      "site.b09eea5a1f8bf16685": "Make the output more useful",
      "site.e9895ac0ad3e1479a9": "Prompt ideas and a repeatable study loop for getting useful learning results from Debate with a personality on inspir.",
      "site.62656f47e151dcabf2": "Reading an AI response is not the same as learning. After the first answer, ask the mode to make you do something with the idea.",
      "site.0db366bee7d789e937": "Related learning paths",
      "site.34703e01be53e56487": "Request feedback on the part that felt uncertain.",
      "site.d13ed52829ac8f9ae5": "Respond before asking for the solution.",
      "site.725c328ba96c60fa28": "Start with one clear request",
      "site.7b1511f40db7799020": "State the goal in one sentence.",
      "site.1115e8dcfc987db693": "study skills",
      "site.e85f78644fc8f2af1a": "That final recap is important. When you explain the idea back, you reveal what is solid and what is still borrowed from the AI.",
      "site.4ad449386f3d17a72b": "The best learning sessions are adjustable. The debate uses public style and worldview without pretending to know private beliefs.",
      "site.ec8f7e2ce775793bbe": "The fastest way to get value from Debate with a personality is to give the AI a learning job, not just a topic. A topic says what you are interested in. A learning job says what kind of help you need.",
      "site.eb51e27d05cde20872": "Then add a constraint that makes the session more personal:",
      "site.2e70d2b0915c157e36": "Try one of these starters:",
      "site.fda025881ab1d825c7": "Turn the mode into practice",
      "site.27069a04f2fe87017e": "Use Debate with a personality when this is the right mode for the job. If you want a related path, try Talk to a historical person. You can also browse the AI learning blog for study methods, Socratic learning, flashcards, roleplay, and active recall."
