  "blog:socratic-ai-tutor": {
    "sourceHash": "7e26072fe4e5588a56a328afafd717b6d39cf2b49f4b52b85924df79ac569af7",
    "sourceStrings": {
      "site.5418fe11c499220291": "\"Help me reason through this ethical dilemma without pushing me to a hidden conclusion.\"",
      "site.352966c547ac088b1a": "\"Help me understand opportunity cost by asking one question at a time.\"",
      "site.c773f2a3284acba81b": "\"I think I understand photosynthesis. Ask questions until you find the weak spot.\"",
      "site.964b9d6e727c2dd845": "\"Make me summarize the final insight in my own words.\"",
      "site.f7fd15ce0e15c12b54": "\"Test whether my argument is valid. Do not give me the answer too quickly.\"",
      "site.eaaffc61ea520eb649": "A direct explanation can be useful. But sometimes the best way to understand an idea is to wrestle with it.",
      "site.87b0c467ed80ade449": "A Socratic tutor can surface those gaps without turning the session into a lecture.",
      "site.7a0d3765af27915bc5": "A strong session usually has four stages.",
      "site.ff43fb5c5c0f826844": "AI is well suited to patient repetition. It can ask the next question, rephrase a hint, change the difficulty, and wait while the learner tries.",
      "site.809d1e1957710315a3": "AI tutor",
      "site.51320c3214deb3e7cc": "Apply the idea to a new example.",
      "site.9413c5736b4da64196": "Can you test that idea with a simple example?",
      "site.d73813ec75bef0b1f5": "critical thinking",
      "site.239a1681ee458f631a": "First, the tutor identifies the target. \"I want to understand opportunity cost\" is different from \"I need to solve this economics homework question\" or \"I need to defend a position in debate.\" The target shapes the questions.",
      "site.5767a106a35eac9d22": "For more practice, pair this with the Socratic Instruction guide, the Socratic prompts and study loop, or the broader guide on studying with AI without cheating yourself.",
      "site.87d186c70c40994969": "Fourth, the tutor asks one next-best question. Not five questions. Not a lecture. One move that keeps the learner thinking.",
      "site.12172064ab44019034": "Good Socratic prompts ask:",
      "site.2d24058f88b11ae757": "How to know it worked",
      "site.847d04773c3bdcbdd4": "Name the misconception or assumption that changed.",
      "site.e6f5db8a4f933a2b88": "Prompts to try",
      "site.70bc8bc72d32fcb39d": "Questions reveal the shape of confusion. A learner might know a formula but not when to use it. They might remember a historical fact but not understand the cause. They might have a strong opinion but weak evidence.",
      "site.55e96beff0827173d3": "Second, the tutor asks a diagnostic question. It should be simple enough to answer but revealing enough to expose the learner's current model.",
      "site.6b301fd9e1520bf0c0": "Socratic learning",
      "site.88f15ed7c65ba44840": "Socratic tutoring is not always the answer. If a learner has no background at all, a short explanation may be kinder than a question. If they are in crisis before a deadline, a planning mode like Exam Prep Planner or a hint mode like Homework Coach may be better. If the goal is remembering terms, Flashcard Builder is more direct.",
      "site.50de465a2e853df96b": "Socratic tutoring uses questions, hypotheses, hints, and reflection to build deeper understanding than passive answer reading.",
      "site.7c86fb8a96c6cb04ac": "State the idea more clearly than at the start.",
      "site.167146118d846317c2": "That is the strength of Socratic learning. Instead of handing over the full answer immediately, the tutor asks a focused question. The learner makes a guess. The tutor tests that guess, offers a hint, and helps the learner notice what changed.",
      "site.84da0a4e3ebacc8dae": "That is what inspir's Socratic Instruction mode is built for: one question at a time, with hints before answers and synthesis after genuine thinking.",
      "site.8807179517ed4961f8": "That is why a Socratic AI tutor can feel slower at first and more powerful later. It trades the comfort of a finished explanation for the evidence that the learner is actually building the idea.",
      "site.54759fbf425cba5ecf": "That rhythm is especially useful for abstract topics: opportunity cost, causation in history, literary interpretation, ethical tradeoffs, proof, probability, and argument structure. It can also support practical work. A learner can use Debate Any Topic after a Socratic session to test whether their reasoning survives pressure.",
      "site.9a219773d3070c6b37": "The important constraint is restraint. A Socratic AI tutor should not dump the answer at the first sign of struggle. It should make effort easier to sustain.",
      "site.994f12f48c17151b99": "The last prompt matters. Socratic learning should end with synthesis. After the questions, the learner should be able to say what changed in their thinking.",
      "site.18abb6aff0f8a17d0a": "The point is not to make every lesson a puzzle. The point is to choose the right amount of struggle.",
      "site.4af2ce3751dcec34b4": "The work happens in the learner's mind.",
      "site.018311ea100e46db7a": "Third, the tutor reads the answer. A useful AI tutor should not merely say \"correct\" or \"incorrect.\" It should identify the claim, the assumption, the gap, or the misconception.",
      "site.299200dd7de534cd1a": "Try it directly in Socratic Instruction. If you want a gentler explanation first, start with Learn Anything, then move into Socratic questions once you know the basic vocabulary.",
      "site.07e374866d8070f138": "Use these prompts in Socratic Instruction:",
      "site.e1e106f63bbbc8bd3b": "What a good Socratic session looks like",
      "site.994831c82791ad6f05": "What do you think is happening?",
      "site.50c9f2f00a083f86b4": "What evidence supports that?",
      "site.5d87e0b2c178c83a36": "What would change your mind?",
      "site.23ed22107e266940e1": "When Socratic tutoring is the wrong tool",
      "site.4335b162337ad74d7f": "Where AI can help",
      "site.1881624eb98fd1038a": "Which assumption is doing the most work?",
      "site.9884d6321db182435a": "Why a Socratic AI tutor can make ideas stick",
      "site.25f4f1d4c8936dc3d0": "Why questions help",
      "site.c94e43c9c2d97a9af5": "You know a Socratic AI tutor worked when the learner can do three things:"
    }
  },
