      "site.e85f78644fc8f2af1a": "That final recap is important. When you explain the idea back, you reveal what is solid and what is still borrowed from the AI.",
      "site.007da0d5fec34b8de8": "The best learning sessions are adjustable. The tutor asks one question at a time, waits for your reasoning, and synthesizes only after you have tried.",
      "site.383226646c99ad6dd2": "The fastest way to get value from Socratic Instruction is to give the AI a learning job, not just a topic. A topic says what you are interested in. A learning job says what kind of help you need.",
      "site.eb51e27d05cde20872": "Then add a constraint that makes the session more personal:",
      "site.2e70d2b0915c157e36": "Try one of these starters:",
      "site.fda025881ab1d825c7": "Turn the mode into practice",
      "site.4cf3a926ba31474f03": "Use Socratic Instruction when this is the right mode for the job. If you want a related path, try Learn Anything. You can also browse the AI learning blog for study methods, Socratic learning, flashcards, roleplay, and active recall."
